title: Definitions
context: PART XI. FEDERAL AND STATE SURPLUS PROPERTY [ยง103D-1101] Definitions. As used in this part, unless the context clearly requires otherwise: &ldquo;Personal property&rdquo; means all tangible goods, including equipment, materials and supplies, except land, buildings, and improvement to the land. &ldquo;Surplus personal property&rdquo; means any personal property that no longer has any use to this State or personal property acquired from the United States government. &ldquo;Surplus personal property&rdquo; includes obsolete, scrap, and excess personal property that has completed its useful life cycle. [L 1994, c 186, pt of ยง1]
